brief_summary: To determine if nonpharmacological interventions, including diet and lifestyle change, could prevent increases in arterial blood pressure leading to systemic hypertension.
condition: Cardiovascular Diseases Heart Diseases Hypertension Vascular Diseases
eligibility_criteria: Men and women, ages 30 to 54, with high normal diastolic blood pressure between 83 and 89 mm Hg. Subjects were mildly obese.
